The paper deals with resource allocation and throughput scaling in large multiuser networks, which are topics typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on cognitive networks, which involve the sharing of spectrum bands between primary and secondary users, making the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category a likely fit as well. The paper also mentions the use of distributed algorithms, which could fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses fairness among secondary users, which is a topic often studied in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
